<div class="space-y-8">
  <section class="space-y-2">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Basics</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      LongShot is a flexible golf pool for PGA Tour events. Create a pool, add one or more upcoming tournaments,
      and invite friends to make their picks.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
      <li>Each pool can include one or more PGA Tour tournaments.</li>
      <li>For each tournament in the pool, every member makes 4 picks.</li>
      <li>Scores for all tournaments in the pool are added together for the final standings.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-2">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">How to Win</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      You earn points from the prize money your picks win. Picking long-odds players pays off with a bonus—so the name fits.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      Your score per pick is <strong>prize money + odds bonus</strong>—but the bonus only counts if your pick
      <strong>makes the cut</strong>. The bonus is <strong>20× the odds</strong> (locked when the tournament starts).
      Think of a long shot at +4500 who sneaks into the weekend: they earn a <strong>90,000-point bonus</strong> (4500 × 20)
      plus whatever prize money they take home. If your pick misses the cut, you get 0 points for that pick. Longer odds mean a bigger bonus when your pick performs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-2">
  </section>
</div>

